{"id": "2026-07-08-news-vaud-court-annuls-immediate-dismissal-of-two-lau", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Vaud court annuls immediate dismissal of two Lausanne police officers over racist WhatsApp messages", "summary": "The Vaud cantonal administrative court (CDAP) voided the immediate firing of two Lausanne officers, ruling the racist and sexist messages justified dismissal but the city acted too slowly to notify them.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/suisse/vaud/les-licenciements-de-deux-policiers-lausannois-annules-par-le-tribunal-cantonal", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Cour de droit administratif et public (CDAP), in two rulings dated 2 July and published Tuesday, found that the officers' years of racist and sexist WhatsApp exchanges were grave and shocking and did justify firing, but that the City of Lausanne waited too long to formally notify the two men that they were being let go, a procedural defect that voids the immediate dismissal. Four officers were originally fired in the scandal, made public at a 25 August 2025 press conference. Police councillor Pierre-Antoine Hildbrand says he will ask his colleagues on the executive to take the case to the Tribunal federal.", "why": "A discipline case that shocked French-speaking Switzerland now turns on process rather than substance; the city could be forced to rehire or compensate officers it judged unfit.", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-lausanne-police-discrimination-le-temps-traces-h", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-02", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-geneva-says-june-s-g7-at-evian-cost-the-canton-3", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Geneva says June's G7 at Evian cost the canton 31.6 million francs", "summary": "Geneva State Councillor Carole-Anne Kast put the canton's G7 bill at 31.6 million francs and said France should cover about 20 million of it.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/suisse/geneve/le-g7-a-coute-31-6-millions-de-francs-a-geneve-selon-carole-anne-kast", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "economy"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Geneva State Councillor Carole-Anne Kast said the summit across the French border cost the canton 31.6 million francs: 12.5 million covered by the Confederation, 13 million in police overtime for roughly 1,500 officers, ~1 million for damage, 3 million for other security and ~500,000 for cybersecurity. Geneva still wants France to cover the remaining ~20 million, but Paris has so far declined; Kast warned the standoff could weigh on regional relations. A business federation (FER) estimates 300 million francs in lost economic activity.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-08-news-geneva-says-june-s-g7-at-evian-cost-the-canton-3", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-08", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-doctors-bristle-at-proposed-cap-on-medical-tarif", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Doctors bristle at proposed cap on medical tariffs under Tardoc", "summary": "The Swiss doctors' association FMH submitted, at the Federal Council's request, a proposal to cap outpatient fees under the new Tardoc system, and physicians warn it could ration care.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/tardoc-le-plafonnement-tarifaire-provoque-beaucoup-d-emotion-chez-les-medecins", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "health"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "At the Federal Council's request, the FMH (the Swiss doctors' association) has submitted, together with the main tariff partners, a proposal to cap outpatient medical fees under Tardoc, the new per-service billing system that replaces the two-decade-old Tarmed catalogue. Physicians warn the ceiling could translate into rationing of care.", "why": "Outpatient costs are a major driver of the health premiums Swiss households pay, so how the cap is set feeds directly into next year's premium debate.", "thread_id": "2026-07-08-news-doctors-bristle-at-proposed-cap-on-medical-tarif", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-08", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-economiesuisse-reopens-the-nuclear-vs-solar-subs", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Economiesuisse reopens the nuclear-vs-solar subsidy fight", "summary": "The business lobby argued that new nuclear plants would need fewer public subsidies than expanding solar, a pointed intervention in Switzerland's energy debate.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/le-debat-sur-le-nucleaire-se-poursuit-selon-economiesuisse-la-construction-de-nouvelles-centrales-necessite-moins-de-subventions-que-pour-le-solaire", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "economy"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "The business lobby argued that building new nuclear plants would need fewer public subsidies than expanding solar, a pointed intervention in the debate over how Switzerland replaces its ageing reactors and hits its decarbonisation targets after voters reopened the door to new nuclear.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-08-news-economiesuisse-reopens-the-nuclear-vs-solar-subs", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-08", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-trump-declares-iran-truce-over-as-us-strikes-doz", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Trump declares Iran truce 'over' as US strikes dozens of targets and Iran hits Gulf bases", "summary": "The US struck 80+ sites in Iran and reinstated oil sanctions after Iranian attacks on ships in the Strait of Hormuz; Iran hit US bases in Bahrain and Kuwait, Trump called the ceasefire over, and Khamenei's funeral began in Najaf.", "url": "https://apnews.com/article/iran-us-israel-war-oil-july-8-2026-fee04dcea661c08de12c04914ff2751b", "source_domain": "apnews.com", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["new source"], "topics": ["geopolitics", "world"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "The US launched strikes on multiple sites across Iran (SRF puts it at more than 80 targets) and reinstated sanctions on Iran's oil exports, saying it was responding to Iranian attacks on three ships in the Strait of Hormuz, the chokepoint through which roughly a fifth of the world's seaborne oil passes. Iran retaliated against American military sites in Bahrain and Kuwait. President Trump called the interim ceasefire over and Iran vicious, violent, though he added he would let negotiations continue; oil prices jumped. Separately, funeral events for Iran's slain Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei got under way in Najaf, Iraq.", "why": "After three weeks of a shaky pause, the two sides are trading fire again and the one man who paused it is now publicly unsure it holds, with the Hormuz oil route back in the crosshairs.", "thread_id": "2026-06-20-cyber-papers-iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-again-over-israeli", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-20", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-ukraine-strikes-russian-oil-and-shadow-fleet-tan", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Ukraine strikes Russian oil and shadow-fleet tankers as fresh missiles hit Kyiv", "summary": "Ukrainian drones struck Russia's Saratov refinery and nine more shadow-fleet tankers in the Azov Sea, while Russian ballistic missiles killed one in Kyiv overnight.", "url": "https://kyivindependent.com/ukraine-hit-another-9-russian-shadow-fleet-tankers-in-azov-sea-energy-facilities-in-crimea-military-say/", "source_domain": "kyivindependent.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Ukraine's military said its long-range drones struck Russia's Saratov oil refinery and hit nine more vessels of Russia's shadow fleet, the ageing tankers Moscow uses to move oil around sanctions, in the Azov Sea, along with energy sites in occupied Crimea. Overnight, Russian ballistic missiles struck Kyiv, killing one woman and injuring two, with strikes also reported on Odesa.", "why": "Kyiv is increasingly hitting the export infrastructure that funds Russia's war, even as it remains largely defenceless against Russia's fastest ballistic missiles.", "thread_id": "2026-05-20-cyber-papers-russia-ukraine-largest-aerial-campaign-of-the-wa", "first_seen_date": "2026-05-20", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-marine-le-pen-convicted-on-appeal-but-stays-elig", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Marine Le Pen convicted on appeal but stays eligible, launches 2027 run", "summary": "A Paris appeals court upheld Le Pen's EU-funds conviction on 7 July but left her eligible; she launched a 2027 presidential campaign on a 'Trumpian' ticket with Bardella.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/avec-sa-candidature-a-la-presidentielle-de-2027-marine-le-pen-la-miraculee-place-la-france-en-territoire-inconnu-analyse-la-presse", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["politics", "world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "A Paris appeals court on Tuesday 7 July upheld a conviction against Le Pen in the EU-funds misuse case yet left her eligible to stand, clearing the bar that could have barred her from the April 2027 presidential election. She promptly opened her campaign on a self-described Trumpian ticket alongside party chief Jordan Bardella, saying I'm not playing for time.", "why": "The ruling many expected to end her career instead frees France's far-right leader to run again, leaving real uncertainty over her actual chances.", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-france-s-appeal-court-rules-tuesday-on-marine-le", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-08-news-venezuela-earthquake-toll-jumps-to-3-685-as-cara", "date": "2026-07-08", "stream": "news", "headline": "Venezuela earthquake toll jumps to 3,685 as Caracas moves to reopen its airport", "summary": "Authorities revised the 24 June double-earthquake toll to 3,685 dead and 16,740 injured and announced plans to resume commercial flights from Caracas.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/les-seismes-au-venezuela-ont-fait-3685-morts-le-gouvernement-presse-pour-rouvrir-l-aeroport-de-caracas", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Authorities revised the toll from the 24 June double earthquake sharply upward, to 3,685 dead and 16,740 injured, and the interim president announced the immediate activation of a plan to resume commercial flights from Caracas's main airport as soon as possible. The government avoids counting the missing; the UN warns the true toll could climb far higher, with projections ranging from about 10,000 to 50,000.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-06-26-cyber-papers-powerful-earthquakes-devastate-venezuela-toll-ri", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-26", "event_date": "2026-06-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
